HPSBMA02667 SSRT100464 rev.3 - HP SiteScope, Cross Site Scripting (XSS) and HTML Injection

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2011-04-21
Last Updated: 2011-05-03

Potential Security Impact: Cross Site Scripting (XSS) and HTML injection

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with HP SiteScope. These vulnerabilities could be exploited remotely via Cross Site Scripting (XSS) and HTML injection.

References: CVE-2011-1726 (XSS), CVE-2011-1727 (HTML injection)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
SiteScope v9.54, v10.13, 11.01, v11.1 running on Windows, Linux and Solaris

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2011-1726    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N)       4.3
CVE-2011-1727    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:N)       5.8
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

The vulnerability can be resolved in HP SiteScope v11.1 by applying the SS1110110412 hotfix available by contacting your HP Support channel.

Note: The hotfix is contained in the SiteScope 11.10 Cumulative fixes available on the HP Software Support Online (SSO) at http://support.openview.hp.com/ Platform
 Patch kit name

IntelLinux
 SIS_00133

SparcSOL
 SIS_00134

Windows
 SIS_00135

For other impacted versions:

Upgrade to v11.1
apply the SS1110110412 hotfix available by contacting your HP Support channel.

